cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of traffic sign detection using deep learning techniques. The use of templates and arbitrary natural images for database generation also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The fact that the problem domain is related to autonomous driving indicates that it could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning for object detection and the potential for security applications suggest that it could belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
